ecs with `refs/meta/config`.\n- Connects to the remote with `Direction::Push`.\n- Calls `ref_map(...)`.\n- Returns `true` if remote refs are non-empty.\n\nThe important bit: this is a network/remote probe, and it can trigger credential, URL, SSH, HTTP, and remote capability failures just to decide whether to show an optional Gerrit prompt.\n\n## Telemetry Caveat\n\nThe UI intends the Gerrit detection failure t\n[TRUNCATED]\note and requesting `refs/meta/config`. That makes sense as a strong signal, but it is overkill for a UI hint. On many private repositories, this requires credentials or fails noisily.\n\nFor a \"does this smell like Gerrit?\" prompt, network failures should probably be treated as \"unknown / false\", not telemetry-worthy errors.\n\n## Suggested Fix Directions\n\nPick one:\n\n1. Best quick fix: make `areYouGerritKiddingMe` suppress telemetry errors.\n   - Add an option to query hooks or endpoint metadata to avoid `emitQueryError`.\n   - Use it for this endpoint because the UI already treats failure as silent.\n\n2. Better product fix: make `is_gerrit` return `false` or `Unknown` for non-actionable probe failures.\n   - `No push remotes found`\n   - credential prompt unavailable\n   - credentials rejected\n   - clear-text HTTP credential refusal\n   - invalid remote URL\n   - DNS/SSH/network failures\n   - smart/dumb protocol mismatch\n\n3. Better architecture fix: avoid live network auth probes for onboarding hints.\n   - Prefer cheap remote URL/config heuristics.\n   - Only do the expensive probe after the user opts into Gerrit mode, or behind an explicit \"check\" action.\n\nMy preference: do option 1 immediately to clean release telemetry, then option 3 if Gerrit detection continues to matter.\n\n## Investigation Pointers\n\nStart here:\n\n- `apps/desktop/src/components/onboarding/ProjectSetupTarget.svelte`\n- `apps/desktop/src/lib/project/projectEndpoints.ts`\n- `apps/desktop/src/lib/state/customHooks.svelte`\n- `apps/desktop/src/lib/error/err